stylometry: Decison trees are used to make an important decison.  When making a decision there are many things we have to take into consideration and we can do so with this decision tree.  For example we may have a problem with a good, fair, and poor economy do we market our cookies or do we just do a cookie sale with no marketing.  When you have the probability of a good, fair, and poor economy, and the output when you do market vs. not market through a tree we can come to a solution for each situation.  If it is a poor economy and if you market it only generates 4 more constomers and costs $100 to market the tree will tell you no, not to market in a poor economy.  The decision tree helps us make business decisions  with, for example, marketing in mind as well as the economy.  In the cookie case we may only want to market in a good economy, and dont market in a poor of fair economy, the cost will be higher then the profit in these types of economies.
